      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Here are some tips for cyclists, the egregious violation of which is the prevailing practice among adult cyclists in this city:</p>
        <p>* Stop and wait at red lights.</p>
        <p>* Do not stop in the crosswalk.</p>
        <p>* Observe one-way street rules.</p>
        <p>* Sidewalks are for pedestrians, with the exception of cyclists under age 13.</p>
        <p>AUGUST  MATZDORF  West Village</p>
      </block>
